listManagement::addField()

Description
    public void listManagement::addField(mixed $field [, string $label = NULL [, bool $dupes = FALSE [, bool $blank = FALSE [, bool $email = FALSE [, bool $disabled = FALSE [, string $size = "40" [, string $type = "text" [, array $options = NULL [, bool $readonly = FALSE [, mixed $value = NULL [, string $matchOn = NULL [,  $validate = NULL]]]]]]]]]]]])
    Adds a field, according to the parameters passed to the function, to the class variable, $this->fields[].

Parameters
    field
        This is either an array or a string.
    label
	This is a valid string associated with the specified field.  Default NULL.
    dupes
	Boolean TRUE or FALSE.  Default FALSE.
    blank
	Boolean TRUE or FALSE.  Default FALSE.
    email
	Boolean TRUE or FALSE.  Default FALSE.
    disabled
	Boolean TRUE or FALSE.  Default FALSE.
    size
	String indicating a field's size.  Default 40.
    type
	String indicating a field's type.  Default "text."
    options
	An array containing a field's options.  Default NULL.
    readonly
	Boolean TRUE or FALSE.  Default FALSE.
    value
	Mixed data type.  String, int, or other valid types.  Default NULL.
    matchOn
	Default NULL.
    validate
	Default NULL.

Return Values
    Returns boolean value of TRUE unless $field['field'] hasn't previously been set, in which case the function returns a value of FALSE.

Examples
    Example #1
	<?php
	    ...
	    $listObj->addField($options);
	    ...
	?>

    Example #2
	<?php
	    ...
	    $listObj->addField("firstName","First Name",TRUE);
	    ...
	?>
    
    Example #3
	<?php
	    ...
	    $listObj->addField("active","Active",TRUE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,40,"select",$activeOptions);
	    ...
	?>

    Example #4
	<?php
	    ...
	    $listObj->addField('<a href="'.$_SERVER['PHP_SELF'].'?action=editAccess&amp;user={userName}">Edit</a>',"Access",FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,0,"plainText");
	    ...
	?>

Notes
    Determine exact use of matchOn and validate.

See Also
    listManagement::removeField()
    listManagement::buildFieldListInsert()
    listManagement::buildFieldValueInsert()
    listManagement::disableAllFields()
    listManagement::disableField()
